If `daemon1` has revision 1 and `daemon2` has revision 1, and the same thread is used for both, `cursorFor` will return the `WorkerHandle` from `daemon1` for `daemon2`! 

In the current `TextDaemon` implementation, each daemon has its own threads, so this is not an issue. But it's good practice to check if the frame belongs to the same ledger or at least if it's the same frame instance.

